======================================================================
PART 2: ANALYTICAL FORMULA FOR INTERVAL DISCRIMINANT
======================================================================

The Q-polynomial for Interval has roots Q_k = sin^2(k*(m+1)*pi/p) / sin^2(k*pi/p)
where k=1,...,m and m=(p-1)/2, m+1=(p+1)/2.

Since {k*(m+1) mod p} is a permutation of {1,...,m} (up to sign),
Q_k = sin^2(pi*sigma(k)/p) / sin^2(pi*k/p) for some permutation sigma.

disc = prod_{i<j} (Q_i - Q_j)^2

