======================================================================
PART 4: e_j = C(m+1, j+1) IDENTITY FOR INTERVAL
======================================================================

If the char poly of Q_1,...,Q_m is prod_{k=1}^m (t - Q_k),
and e_j = C(m+1, j+1), then the char poly is:
  t^m - C(m+1,2)*t^{m-1} + C(m+1,3)*t^{m-2} - ... + (-1)^m * C(m+1,m+1)
  = t^m - C(m+1,2)*t^{m-1} + ... + (-1)^m * 1

This is the Chebyshev-like polynomial arising from sin^2 ratios!

